{"word":"H5518 - סִיר - çîyr - seer - Caldron","slug":"H5518","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">סִיר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>çîyr"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>seer"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Caldron"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E1;&#x05E8;&#x05D4;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E1;&#x05D9;&#x05E8;&#x05D4;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E1;&#x05D9;&#x05E8; - s&#x0131;&#x0302;yr  s&#x0131;&#x0302;yra&#x0302;h  sira&#x0302;h</b> - <i>seer, see-raw', see-raw'</i><p/>From a primitive root meaning to <i>boil</i> up; a <i>pot</i>; also a <i>thorn</i> (as springing up rapidly); by implication a <i>hook: - </i>caldron, fishhook, pan, ([wash-]) pot, thorn."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4536\">H4536</a>, <a href=\"#/H5503\">H5503</a>, <a href=\"#/H5504\">H5504</a>, <a href=\"#/H5505\">H5505</a>, <a href=\"#/H5506\">H5506</a>, <a href=\"#/H5507\">H5507</a>, <a href=\"#/H5508\">H5508</a>, <a href=\"#/H5510\">H5510</a>, <a href=\"#/H5511\">H5511</a>, <a href=\"#/H5512\">H5512</a>, <a href=\"#/H5513\">H5513</a>, <a href=\"#/H5514\">H5514</a>, <a href=\"#/H5515\">H5515</a>, <a href=\"#/H5516\">H5516</a>, <a href=\"#/H5517\">H5517</a>, <a href=\"#/H5522\">H5522</a>, <a href=\"#/H5524\">H5524</a>, <a href=\"#/H5525\">H5525</a>"}]}